node.text: Photos by Amy Sacka @amysacka | How do you make a lighthouse interesting? We've see them over and over, the images of these beautiful structures on postcards and touristy images. I drove into this park in Tawas, Michigan late at night, knowing there would not be much light. I turned my headlights onto the gate, which created these beautiful shadows leading to the lighthouse. I believe it enabled me to see this lighthouse anew. #YourShotPhotographer
Photo by Andrei Stoica @ArizonaPhotoAdventures | Sunset over the "Four Peaks", Arizona. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by @DaisyGilardini | The Falkland Islands marks the northernmost limit of the King penguins range. In the morning flocks of penguins gather on the beach before heading out to sea to feed. Kings aren’t picky eaters exactly but they’re very specific about what they hunt and catch. They eat small, schooling fish like lantern (myctophids) fish year-round, especially during breeding season. When the weather grows colder they eat more ice fish and cephalopds — molluscs, octopus and squid — to supplement their winter diet. | SUA Civil Aviation Falkland Islands permit n. 18_OTO_P0378 #yourshotphotographer

Photo by Dene' Miles @denemiles | Reed Flute Cave is a landmark and tourist attraction in China.  It's a natural limestone cave which is also referred to as "the Palace of Natural Arts". The multicolored lighting and water within the cave adds to the otherworldly feel. |  #YourShotPhotographer
Photo by Brittany Crossman @bkcrossman | An Atlantic puffin gathers grass to line the inside of its burrow, Iceland. #YourShotPhotographer
Photo by Aya Okawa @labyrinthiansmile | California Agriculture. Such precision in these Southern California orchards, photographed from a small plane just before sunset.

Photo by Tianyuan Xiao |  I was travelling from Sacramento to Yosemite on Christmas day, but was trapped in traffic. When I got there, sunset was already gone, which is what I planned to shoot. I was very sad at that moment because that was my only chance in this trip to shoot sunset at Tunnel View. But a few minutes later, I noticed the light path formed by the cars was a great leading line to the valley during the blue hour, and a  little bit fog was just formed above the road which made it even better. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Dene' Miles @denemiles | For three weekends in December, the Bavarian style mountain town of Leavenworth, WA has their tree lighting festival. It usually includes snow and lots of Santa sightings. | #YourShotPhotographer
Photo by @meg_nlo | Trimming the tree. One day I'm going to miss the ornament clusters of this perfectly imperfect tree. #yourshotphotographer

Photograph by Steve Woods @steve_woods_photography / An early morning sunrise view of Moraine Lake in the Valley of the Ten Peaks, Banff national park, Alberta, Canada. After recently relocating to Canada, I wanted to see this place for myself. Over a few days I walked around and photographed it at different times and different locations getting a feel for the place. This was a particularly crisp -20ºc morning. I found a glacial boulder to climb up onto and set up my shot, though this meant standing pretty much still for over 3hrs before the sun rose. This made the arrival of the first beams of intense red sunlight into a beautiful clear sky even more climactic. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Victor Lima @victorlimaphoto | Vertical Panorama maded on the Baltinache Lagoon in the Atacama Desert in Chile. The seven small saltwater lagoons that emerge in the middle of the Atacama Salt Flat have the density of their water higher than that of the Dead Sea in Jordan #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Haitham AL Farsi @farsihaitham | This historic 2,450 metre-long falaj is located in Barkat Al Mouz, Nizwa, and is famous for having a unique water distribution system and continuity of flow throughout the year. It’s fascinating to see how one of its channels passes through Al Radeeda fortress on its way to the farmlands. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Anuar Patjane Floriuk @anuarpatjane | Protecting a few spots in the Sea of Cortés, like Cabo Pulmo (Mexico), has been yielding amazing results in the last few years: a constant increase of biomass inside the protected areas is noticeable and also an increase in the variety of life. Not only sea life benefits from this; so does fishermen outside the protected areas and the local economy that relies now on ecotourism instead of fishing. Now other areas are following this example. | When photographing huge schools of fish or big animals, I concentrate the compositional effort in the aesthetic of movement instead of getting distracted by the epic nature of the moment. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by John Barton @johnnyjungle | Where the island sinks into the sea. This tranquil headland is one of my favourite views in the Mentawai Islands. I often swim past this headland  on my way to photograph surfers at a nearby wave and I can't help but stop here and float for a while every time I do  just to take it in. | This image was taken with a waterproof housing for my camera and a large flat lens port to allow the watery perspective. #yourshotphotographer
Photo by Matt Hage @HagePhoto | Dana checking out the 'blue light special' winter biking around a glacier in South Central Alaska. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by @daisygilardini | Being in the right place at the right time is key when on assignment in remote locations. A sailboat is an incredible platform for photography in Antarctica’s  frozen waters, even if sometimes it’s not the most comfortable and stable means of transportation — especially if you suffer from seasickness. The flexibility of cruising among icebergs in shallow water, and the lower angle one gets when close to the water, are simply brilliant. | Shot with drone permit NCR-0001 - Environment and Climate Change Canada under the Antarctic Environmental Protection Act (EPA). #yourshotphotographer
Photograph by Mary McGowan | #YourShotPhotographer Mary McGowan photographed this moment of two black skimmer chicks who were having a tug ‘o war with a small fish.

Photo by @taylorthomasalbright | Clumsily wading through a clear Alaskan river, a brown bear keeps its eyes focused on the school of salmon swimming just beyond its reach. Without warning those meandering steps turn into a fierce charge, bursting into the air diving forward head first with outstretched arms onto the salmon creating an explosion of water. | Typically younger, inexperienced and less dominant bears frequent the shallow water areas, as the larger dominant bears use more efficient techniques for catching fish. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Takashi Nakazawa @takashi_photography) | The moment that Mt Fuji appeared through clouds. It looked like a ship floating up from the bottom of the sea of clouds. Amazingly wonderful view. #YourShotPhotographer
Photo by Pavel Tkachuk | A car drifts into a turn during the Russian Drift Series GP, Stage 1 in Moscow, Russia. #yourshotphotographer

Photograph by Ivan Lesica @ivan_lesica | While walking around New York city I noticed a giant hand on the metal wall/door. I decided to wait and try to capture a person right in between the fingers and after few tries and about 20 min I achieved my goal. One thing that I can say that I am is patient . If I see a photo opportunity I will wait for a perfect moment as long as it takes and take hundreds of photos to get the " right one".
#yourshotphotographer

Photo by Juan Carlos Fajardo @jc_fajardo | A close-up portrait of a black vulture, one of the most threatened and one of the largest vultures, with a wingspan of almost 3 meters. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Jorge Cervera Hauser @jchauser | Don't feel limited by your gear or equipment, this image of a blue whale was taken using a smartphone on a very simpke housing freediving at 45ft way out in the open ocean off Baja, Mexico  #yourshotphotographer
Photo by Matt Hage @HagePhoto | Vortex hunting in the sandstone spires around Sedona, Arizona. #YourShotPhotographer
Photo by Dene' Miles @denemiles | Frozen trees and fresh tracks on one of the many popular ski resorts outside Vancouver, BC. #YourShotPhotographer
